WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.910 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.910 --> 00:00:08.347 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:08.347 --> 00:00:10.330 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.330 --> 00:00:11.950 align:middle line:84%
>>HARLEY ROTBART:
My current career

00:00:11.950 --> 00:00:15.405 align:middle line:84%
as a inspirational
writer, if you will,

00:00:15.405 --> 00:00:18.040 align:middle line:84%
is very different
than my first career

00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:21.057 align:middle line:84%
as a evidence-based
clinician and scientist.

00:00:21.057 --> 00:00:23.140 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: You've
seen miracles in your life,

00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:23.770 align:middle line:90%
haven't you?

00:00:23.770 --> 00:00:24.570 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: I have.

00:00:24.570 --> 00:00:28.300 align:middle line:84%
That gap between scientific
knowledge and what's

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:32.710 align:middle line:84%
really out there is where
there's room for God.

00:00:32.710 --> 00:00:34.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Who creates
the miracles?

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:37.600 align:middle line:84%
Is it us, or are we
tapping into something?

00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:39.640 align:middle line:84%
>>ROTBART: The capacity
to create miracles

00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:41.410 align:middle line:90%
exists within every one of us.

00:00:41.410 --> 00:00:44.320 align:middle line:84%
We don't know who's going to
be affected by what we do.

00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:46.970 align:middle line:84%
But people are going to
be affected by what we do.

00:00:46.970 --> 00:00:50.080 align:middle line:84%
And that's where we
can create miracles.

00:00:50.080 --> 00:00:53.419 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:53.419 --> 00:00:54.440 align:middle line:90%


00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:56.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:56.190 --> 00:01:00.090 align:middle line:10%
Dr. Harley Rotbart is back with
us, an internationally renowned

00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:02.230 align:middle line:10%
infectious disease specialist.

00:01:02.230 --> 00:01:05.340 align:middle line:84%
He's a pediatrician,
a parenting expert,

00:01:05.340 --> 00:01:08.790 align:middle line:84%
a speaker of all things
great, and an educator.

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:12.120 align:middle line:84%
He's a professor and vice chair
Emeritus at the University

00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:15.240 align:middle line:84%
of Colorado School of
Medicine, author of more than--

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:16.230 align:middle line:90%
get this--

00:01:16.230 --> 00:01:21.690 align:middle line:84%
175 medical and scientific
publications, as well as

00:01:21.690 --> 00:01:24.420 align:middle line:84%
at least five books
for general audiences.

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:26.790 align:middle line:84%
How many books do you have
out there, five or more?

00:01:26.790 --> 00:01:27.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Six now.

00:01:27.630 --> 00:01:28.922 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's what I thought.

00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:29.970 align:middle line:90%
My god, they keep coming.

00:01:29.970 --> 00:01:30.280 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: [CHUCKLES]

00:01:30.280 --> 00:01:32.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And the name
of the latest book is--

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:33.332 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: "No Regrets Living--

00:01:33.332 --> 00:01:35.293 align:middle line:84%
7 Keys to a Life of
Wonder and Contentment."

00:01:35.293 --> 00:01:37.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And we're going to
go through some of those seven

00:01:37.710 --> 00:01:38.070 align:middle line:90%
keys.

00:01:38.070 --> 00:01:39.480 align:middle line:90%
But Harley, how have you been?

00:01:39.480 --> 00:01:40.620 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Thank you.

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:41.980 align:middle line:10%
It's a pleasure to be here.

00:01:41.980 --> 00:01:44.115 align:middle line:10%
I had a chance to speak
with you on the radio,

00:01:44.115 --> 00:01:45.990 align:middle line:10%
and it's nice to see
you in three dimensions.

00:01:45.990 --> 00:01:48.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We had great response
to you when you were on "Coast

00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:49.410 align:middle line:90%
to Coast"--

00:01:49.410 --> 00:01:49.800 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Thank you.

00:01:49.800 --> 00:01:51.075 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --just
absolutely stunning

00:01:51.075 --> 00:01:51.930 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Thank you.

00:01:51.930 --> 00:01:53.305 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did
you get involved

00:01:53.305 --> 00:01:56.120 align:middle line:90%
in the field you're in today?

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:59.830 align:middle line:10%
>>ROTBART: Well,
my current career

00:01:59.830 --> 00:02:04.280 align:middle line:10%
as a sort of inspirational
[CHUCKLES] writer, if you will,

00:02:04.280 --> 00:02:07.360 align:middle line:10%
is very different
than my first career

00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:11.170 align:middle line:10%
as a evidence-based
clinician and scientist.

00:02:11.170 --> 00:02:16.240 align:middle line:84%
And it really began
about 40 years ago

00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:19.840 align:middle line:90%
with two parallel motivations.

00:02:19.840 --> 00:02:24.340 align:middle line:84%
One of them was the
death of my dad.

00:02:24.340 --> 00:02:28.750 align:middle line:84%
My dad was a concentration camp
survivor, a European immigrant.

00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:34.270 align:middle line:84%
And he died tragically
of pancreatic cancer

00:02:34.270 --> 00:02:38.080 align:middle line:84%
at a very young age, before he
had a chance to meet my wife,

00:02:38.080 --> 00:02:40.330 align:middle line:90%
to know his grandkids.

00:02:40.330 --> 00:02:43.840 align:middle line:84%
But I also did not have
a chance to know him

00:02:43.840 --> 00:02:45.610 align:middle line:90%
as well as I wish I would have.

00:02:45.610 --> 00:02:49.330 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what his
worldview was coming out

00:02:49.330 --> 00:02:54.700 align:middle line:84%
of the camps on God, on
fate, on the Messiah.

00:02:54.700 --> 00:02:56.680 align:middle line:90%
And I'm sorry I didn't ask.

00:02:56.680 --> 00:02:59.470 align:middle line:84%
I was in the go-go years
of my young adulthood,

00:02:59.470 --> 00:03:03.190 align:middle line:84%
and there just wasn't a lot
of time to sit down and talk.

00:03:03.190 --> 00:03:08.080 align:middle line:84%
And the second motivating factor
was that, also 40 years ago, I

00:03:08.080 --> 00:03:10.630 align:middle line:84%
took care of a child in
the intensive care unit

00:03:10.630 --> 00:03:14.500 align:middle line:84%
at Children's Hospital
in Philadelphia, who,

00:03:14.500 --> 00:03:17.200 align:middle line:84%
for all intents and
purposes, was dead.

00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:20.830 align:middle line:84%
He was in a prolonged coma, was
never going to come out of it.

00:03:20.830 --> 00:03:23.330 align:middle line:84%
Then he walked out of the
hospital fully recovered.

00:03:23.330 --> 00:03:24.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: My god.

00:03:24.130 --> 00:03:25.330 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Exactly.

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:32.770 align:middle line:84%
And those two events
led me to ask colleagues

00:03:32.770 --> 00:03:35.650 align:middle line:84%
if they had had
similar miraculous

00:03:35.650 --> 00:03:40.240 align:middle line:84%
or unexplainable, unforgettable
clinical experiences.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:43.300 align:middle line:84%
And that resulted in a book
five years ago called "Miracles

00:03:43.300 --> 00:03:44.800 align:middle line:90%
We Have Seen" that I wrote.

00:03:44.800 --> 00:03:47.110 align:middle line:84%
And it was a
collection of 85 essays

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:50.890 align:middle line:84%
from the most respected
physicians in the country

00:03:50.890 --> 00:03:55.030 align:middle line:84%
describing cases that
they could never forget,

00:03:55.030 --> 00:03:57.250 align:middle line:84%
the outcomes that they
could never have predicted,

00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:59.380 align:middle line:90%
miraculous cases.

00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:03.400 align:middle line:84%
And those essays were
filled with the dilemma

00:04:03.400 --> 00:04:07.720 align:middle line:84%
of faith versus science,
of belief versus medicine.

00:04:07.720 --> 00:04:09.370 align:middle line:90%
And I wanted to expand on that.

00:04:09.370 --> 00:04:13.840 align:middle line:84%
And the No Regrets Living
Project that I then undertook

00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:18.459 align:middle line:84%
was to try and further explore
the relationship between faith,

00:04:18.459 --> 00:04:22.270 align:middle line:84%
God, and evidence-based
medicine and science.

00:04:22.270 --> 00:04:25.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there a
mixture between the two

00:04:25.150 --> 00:04:26.830 align:middle line:90%
that makes it work?

00:04:26.830 --> 00:04:30.460 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Yes, I believe--

00:04:30.460 --> 00:04:35.050 align:middle line:84%
and I use that
word selectively--

00:04:35.050 --> 00:04:40.840 align:middle line:84%
I believe that science
is evidence for God.

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:44.920 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm an
evidence-based physician,

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:46.390 align:middle line:90%
evidence-based scientist.

00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:48.370 align:middle line:90%
I believe in the Big Bang.

00:04:48.370 --> 00:04:50.120 align:middle line:90%
I believe in science.

00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:53.380 align:middle line:84%
I believe in the science that
I generated in my laboratory

00:04:53.380 --> 00:04:54.230 align:middle line:90%
for many years.

00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:56.060 align:middle line:90%
I believe in that science.

00:04:56.060 --> 00:05:00.610 align:middle line:84%
I believe in it unless and
until it's proven wrong.

00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:03.940 align:middle line:84%
And we think back to
the time of Hippocrates,

00:05:03.940 --> 00:05:06.820 align:middle line:84%
who had the theory of the
four humors and the four

00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:09.850 align:middle line:84%
temperaments, which now as
scientists and physicians,

00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:11.170 align:middle line:90%
we laugh at.

00:05:11.170 --> 00:05:15.070 align:middle line:84%
And someday, we may laugh at
the theory of the Big Bang.

00:05:15.070 --> 00:05:19.120 align:middle line:84%
We may laugh at the
theory of virus origins.

00:05:19.120 --> 00:05:21.580 align:middle line:84%
But for right now, I'm
a believer in science.

00:05:21.580 --> 00:05:25.780 align:middle line:84%
But I'm also a realist,
and I appreciate all

00:05:25.780 --> 00:05:28.660 align:middle line:84%
that we do not learn
from science, everything

00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:30.970 align:middle line:84%
that we'll never
learn from science.

00:05:30.970 --> 00:05:36.310 align:middle line:84%
And that gap between
scientific knowledge and what's

00:05:36.310 --> 00:05:41.080 align:middle line:84%
really out there is where
there's room for God.

00:05:41.080 --> 00:05:42.340 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:45.430 align:middle line:84%
And it's so refreshing
to hear this

00:05:45.430 --> 00:05:48.640 align:middle line:84%
come from a man of
science, because that

00:05:48.640 --> 00:05:50.185 align:middle line:90%
doesn't happen a lot.

00:05:50.185 --> 00:05:52.420 align:middle line:84%
>>ROTBART: [CHUCKLES]
Hearing myself talk

00:05:52.420 --> 00:05:56.080 align:middle line:84%
and trying to project what my
colleagues are hearing when

00:05:56.080 --> 00:05:59.110 align:middle line:84%
they hear me talk,
it might sound

00:05:59.110 --> 00:06:03.430 align:middle line:84%
a little kind of ethereal,
a little mystical.

00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:09.760 align:middle line:84%
And I do have a mystical
sense, but I'm really

00:06:09.760 --> 00:06:12.400 align:middle line:90%
firmly rooted in science.

00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:16.330 align:middle line:84%
And there is nothing,
nothing about anything

00:06:16.330 --> 00:06:19.600 align:middle line:84%
that we know about
science that disproves

00:06:19.600 --> 00:06:22.180 align:middle line:84%
the existence of something
greater out there.

00:06:22.180 --> 00:06:23.950 align:middle line:90%
I don't-- I use the word "God."

00:06:23.950 --> 00:06:25.270 align:middle line:90%
Everyone else has a--

00:06:25.270 --> 00:06:28.540 align:middle line:84%
can have a different
explanation, a different term.

00:06:28.540 --> 00:06:30.710 align:middle line:84%
But there's something
else that's out there.

00:06:30.710 --> 00:06:32.468 align:middle line:84%
There has to be,
because there's so much

00:06:32.468 --> 00:06:34.885 align:middle line:84%
that we don't understand, and
that we'll never understand.

00:06:34.885 --> 00:06:38.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There was a Gaia
program called "Sacred Powers."

00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:43.442 align:middle line:84%
And Caroline Myss talks about
the modern nature of God.

00:06:43.442 --> 00:06:46.170 align:middle line:84%
>>CAROLINE MYSS: How we
understand the nature of God

00:06:46.170 --> 00:06:49.860 align:middle line:84%
is undergoing the most
significant transformation

00:06:49.860 --> 00:06:52.260 align:middle line:90%
in the history of humanity.

00:06:52.260 --> 00:06:57.510 align:middle line:10%
Hi, I'm Carolyn Myss, and we
can't talk about sacred power

00:06:57.510 --> 00:07:00.020 align:middle line:10%
without talking about God.

00:07:00.020 --> 00:07:02.900 align:middle line:10%
Never before has
humanity experienced

00:07:02.900 --> 00:07:06.740 align:middle line:10%
this level of disengagement
from religious traditions,

00:07:06.740 --> 00:07:10.070 align:middle line:10%
or the very question of
the existence of God.

00:07:10.070 --> 00:07:12.170 align:middle line:10%
Now think about that.

00:07:12.170 --> 00:07:15.950 align:middle line:10%
Think about that, the fact
that for the first time

00:07:15.950 --> 00:07:20.840 align:middle line:10%
in the history of humanity,
a vast majority of people

00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:23.480 align:middle line:10%
are questioning the
existence of God.

00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:26.450 align:middle line:84%
For every choice,
there's a consequence.

00:07:26.450 --> 00:07:30.470 align:middle line:84%
What's the consequence
of a high percentage

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:34.070 align:middle line:84%
of people in a
society questioning

00:07:34.070 --> 00:07:36.440 align:middle line:90%
the existence of God?

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:39.980 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not speaking to you
from the position of, let's say,

00:07:39.980 --> 00:07:45.710 align:middle line:84%
fundamentalism, or Armageddon,
where I'm warning you

00:07:45.710 --> 00:07:48.530 align:middle line:84%
that the fires of hell are
going to come raining down,

00:07:48.530 --> 00:07:50.520 align:middle line:84%
because I don't
believe in any of that.

00:07:50.520 --> 00:07:56.790 align:middle line:84%
I just-- I'm talking pure,
mystical law, that there's

00:07:56.790 --> 00:07:59.550 align:middle line:90%
a cause and there's effect.

00:07:59.550 --> 00:08:02.970 align:middle line:10%
There's action and
there's reaction,

00:08:02.970 --> 00:08:06.480 align:middle line:10%
and that we live
in a universe where

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:11.280 align:middle line:10%
our thoughts and our
collective consciousness

00:08:11.280 --> 00:08:16.510 align:middle line:10%
holds together the
world that we live in.

00:08:16.510 --> 00:08:21.540 align:middle line:84%
So when a high percentage
of the population

00:08:21.540 --> 00:08:26.460 align:middle line:84%
begins to question
the nature of God,

00:08:26.460 --> 00:08:29.970 align:middle line:84%
what happens to the
collective, the global,

00:08:29.970 --> 00:08:33.299 align:middle line:84%
the different
pockets of society?

00:08:33.299 --> 00:08:37.230 align:middle line:84%
Anger, division, and disdain
at traditional religion's

00:08:37.230 --> 00:08:41.970 align:middle line:84%
inability to keep up with
the needs of a modern devotee

00:08:41.970 --> 00:08:45.870 align:middle line:84%
has only encouraged people
to become very distant

00:08:45.870 --> 00:08:49.775 align:middle line:84%
from religions that
they've been connected to.

00:08:49.775 --> 00:08:53.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: She's basically telling
us, Harley, as you've said,

00:08:53.380 --> 00:08:55.250 align:middle line:90%
that there is a God.

00:08:55.250 --> 00:08:56.430 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: She is.

00:08:56.430 --> 00:08:59.010 align:middle line:84%
And she's also asking
a critical question

00:08:59.010 --> 00:09:00.690 align:middle line:90%
that I'm going to try to answer.

00:09:00.690 --> 00:09:02.670 align:middle line:90%
And that is, what happens--

00:09:02.670 --> 00:09:07.590 align:middle line:84%
what are the consequences of
people, and increasing numbers

00:09:07.590 --> 00:09:11.490 align:middle line:84%
of people, not believing in
a higher power, in something

00:09:11.490 --> 00:09:13.630 align:middle line:90%
greater than ourselves?

00:09:13.630 --> 00:09:16.710 align:middle line:84%
And the consequences are
in the newspaper every day.

00:09:16.710 --> 00:09:21.135 align:middle line:84%
In the newspaper every day,
we are confronted by evil--

00:09:21.135 --> 00:09:22.845 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Evil, constant.

00:09:22.845 --> 00:09:23.970 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: --absolute evil.

00:09:23.970 --> 00:09:27.660 align:middle line:90%
And I mentioned it earlier.

00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:30.840 align:middle line:84%
The consequence of not believing
in God is the Holocaust.

00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:34.050 align:middle line:84%
It is genocide around the
world after the Holocaust

00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:35.280 align:middle line:90%
and before the Holocaust.

00:09:35.280 --> 00:09:37.120 align:middle line:90%
Its mass shootings.

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:42.420 align:middle line:84%
It is a disregard, a disrespect,
for our fellow humans.

00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:43.260 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:46.770 align:middle line:84%
Because we don't feel
as if we're answerable.

00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:51.060 align:middle line:84%
We don't feel as if there is
a consequence to our actions.

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:55.590 align:middle line:84%
And that is ultimately
the consequence

00:09:55.590 --> 00:09:59.730 align:middle line:84%
of more and more people not
believing in something greater

00:09:59.730 --> 00:10:00.970 align:middle line:90%
than ourselves.

00:10:00.970 --> 00:10:02.817 align:middle line:84%
We are not the be
all and the end all.

00:10:02.817 --> 00:10:04.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I've always
wondered about somebody

00:10:04.650 --> 00:10:07.890 align:middle line:84%
who goes into a factory
or a work environment,

00:10:07.890 --> 00:10:12.420 align:middle line:84%
shoots it up, kills six
people, then kills themself.

00:10:12.420 --> 00:10:13.490 align:middle line:90%
Why do they do that?

00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:16.000 align:middle line:84%
Why don't they just end their
own life first and get over

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:16.800 align:middle line:90%
with it?

00:10:16.800 --> 00:10:17.820 align:middle line:90%
>>ROTBART: Right.

00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:20.670 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a
combination of factors there.

00:10:20.670 --> 00:10:23.790 align:middle line:84%
And I'm by no means
expert in mass shootings,

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:28.890 align:middle line:84%
but I do spend a lot of my
time dealing with human nature.

00:10:28.890 --> 00:10:34.740 align:middle line:84%
And I think that people are
desperate for an impact.

00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:41.100 align:middle line:84%
And if they have no other
recourse to creating impact,

00:10:41.100 --> 00:10:45.900 align:middle line:84%
they choose an impact
that satisfies them,

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:48.430 align:middle line:90%
and then they're done.

00:10:48.430 --> 00:10:49.960 align:middle line:90%
Then they end their own lives.

00:10:49.960 --> 00:10:53.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think people
have to find--

00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:56.880 align:middle line:84%
one of the keys of the
no regrets living concept

00:10:56.880 --> 00:10:59.790 align:middle line:84%
is people have to seek
purpose in their lives.

00:10:59.790 --> 00:11:02.220 align:middle line:84%
And people who have
purpose in their lives

00:11:02.220 --> 00:11:04.200 align:middle line:84%
don't go into factories
and shoot people.

00:11:04.200 --> 00:11:05.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:11:05.000 --> 00:11:07.710 align:middle line:84%
>>ROTBART: They don't
build gas chambers,

00:11:07.710 --> 00:11:09.150 align:middle line:90%
